<font size="2" color="#505050"><br>Well I did it, I pre-registered for the Ykesha patch or whatever it's called.  The screen locked up and I had no idea if it went through or not.  I went into online chat and they couldn't help me, so I contacted SOE customer support.<br>
<br>
They did the unthinkable!  They asked me for my password!  I did not want to give it to them.  The guy.. well.. look see for yourself:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You have been connected to CSR Eric W..<br>
CSR Eric W.: Thanks for using Sony Online Chat Ariza<br>
. This is Eric what may I help you with tonight?<br>
CSR Eric W.: station name and password<br>
Ariza: wow it's already night?<br>
Ariza: station name is (removed)<br>
CSR Eric W.: password<br>
Ariza: you're kidding, right?<br>
CSR Eric W.: you want me to access it and update you right?<br>
Ariza: i've read that SOE staff would never ask me for my 
password, and now you are?<br>
CSR Eric W.: or i can make you a new password your call<br>
Ariza: yeah do that<br>
CSR Eric W.: brb<br>
CSR Eric W.: your good to go<br>
CSR Eric W.: new password (removed)<br>
Ariza: ok thanks<br>
Ariza: but that wasn't my original issue<br>
CSR Eric W.: im talking about your expansion<br>
Ariza: so the pre-registration went through?<br>
Ariza: you should really talk to your supervisor about asking 
people for their passwords, it goes against every rule of good customer 
service.<br>
CSR Eric W.: well its easier then saying try again <br>
CSR Eric W.: Is there anything else I can help you with Tonight?<br>
Ariza: no, i changed the password back to mine, so nothing is 
lost<br>
CSR Eric W.: k<br>
Ariza: thanks<br>
CSR Eric W.: Thanks for using Sony Online Chat Ariza
